article.headline: High Point 88, NC Asheville 67
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Arizona Reid scored 20 points in the second half and finished with 22 as High Point beat N.C.-Asheville 88-67 in Big South Conference on Monday. N.C.-Asheville (9-17, 6-9) was playing its fifth game in 10 days. The Panthers (14-11, 7-7)put the game away midway through the second half. High Point, leading 46-37 with 15 minutes to go, went on an 11-0 run to build a 57-37 lead. Reid scored eight points during the run. High Point shot 62 percent from the field in the second half. Michael Ellis led the Bulldogs with 20 points. Joseph Barber added 11.
